nce%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20stormed%20into%20this%20battle%20with%20new%20features%20that%20help%20websites%20block%20unwanted%20AI%20bot%20crawlers.%20Cloudflare%20is%20an%20infrastructure%2C%20security%2C%20and%20software%20company%20that%20helps%20run%20about%2020%25%20of%20the%20internet.%20It%20thrives%20when%20the%20web%20does%20well%2C%20hence%20its%20interest%20in%20helping%20sites%20get%20paid%20for%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Cloudflare%20customers%20recently%20complained%20to%20the%20company%20that%20Perplexity%20was%20evading%20these%20blocks%20and%20continued%20to%20scrape%20and%20collect%20data%20without%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20CloudFlare%20set%20a%20digital%20trap%20and%20caught%20this%20startup%20red-handed%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Monday%20blog%20describing%20the%20escapade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20supposedly%20'reputable'%20AI%20companies%20act%20more%20like%20North%20Korean%20hackers%2C%26quot%3B%20Prince%20wrote%20on%20X%20on%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BTime%20to%20name%2C%20shame%2C%20and%20hard%20block%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerplexity%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a826e464-d550-4208-bb86-21dff60dfcc0%5C%22%3EThe%20bait%3A%20Honeytrap%20domains%20and%20locked%20doors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECloudflare%20created%20entirely%20new%2C%20unpublished%20websites%20and%20configured%20them%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-killing-web-grand-bargain-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erobots.txt%20files%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20explicitly%20blocked%20all%20crawlers%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Perplexity's%20declared%20bots%2C%20%3Cem%3EPerplexityBot%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EPerplexity-User%3C%2Fem%3E.%20These%20test%20sites%20had%20no%20public%20links%2C%20search%20engine%20entries%2C%20or%20metadata%20that%20would%20normally%20make%20them%20discoverable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20when%20Cloudflare%20queried%20Perplexity's%20AI%20with%20questions%20about%20these%20specific%20sites%2C%20the%20startup's%20service%20responded%20with%20detailed%20information%20that%20could%20only%20have%20come%20from%20those%20restricted%20pages.%20The%20conclusion%3F%20Perplexity%20had%20accessed%20the%20content%20despite%20being%20clearly%20told%20not%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8257860-7598-450b-aa85-d3acd54a0cf6%5C%22%3EThe%20cloak%3A%20How%20Perplexity%20masked%20its%20crawl%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPerplexity%20initially%20crawled%20these%20sites%20using%20its%20official%20user-agent%20string%2C%20complying%20with%20standard%20protocols.%20However%2C%20Cloudflare%20said%20it%20discovered%20that%20once%20blocked%2C%20Perplexity%20resorted%20to%20stealth%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECloudflare%20found%20that%20Perplexity%20began%20deploying%20undeclared%20crawlers%20disguised%20as%20normal%20web%20browsers%20and%20sending%20requests%20from%20unknown%20or%20rotated%20IP%20addresses%20and%20unofficial%20ASNs%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhich%20are%20crucial%20identifiers%20that%20help%20route%20internet%20traffic%20efficiently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20its%20official%20crawlers%20were%20blocked%2C%20Perplexity%20also%20used%20a%20generic%20web%20browser%20designed%20to%20impersonate%20Google's%20Chrome%20browser%20on%20Apple%20Mac%20computers.%C2%A0%3Cs%3E(%3C%2Fs%3EBusiness%20Insider%20asked%20Google%20whether%20it%20has%20told%20Perplexity%20to%20stop%20impersonating%20Chrome.%20Google%20did%20not%20respond).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Cloudflare%2C%20Perplexity%20has%20been%20making%20millions%20of%20such%20%26quot%3Bstealth%26quot%3B%20requests%20daily%20across%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20web%20domains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20behavior%20not%20only%20violated%20web%20standards%2C%20but%20also%20betrays%20the%20fundamental%20trust%20that%20underpins%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20open%20web%2C%20Cloudflare%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223fff7c45-ccd3-431d-b4d8-51ac1f1152b9%5C%22%3EThe%20comparison%3A%20How%20OpenAI%20gets%20it%20right%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20emphasize%20what%20good%20bot%20behavior%20looks%20like%2C%20Cloudflare%20compared%20Perplexity's%20conduct%20to%20that%20of%20OpenAI's%20crawlers%2C%20which%20scrape%20data%20for%20developing%20ChatGPT%20and%20giant%20AI%20models%20such%20as%20the%20upcoming%20GPT-5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20OpenAI's%20bots%20encountered%20a%20robots.txt%20file%20or%20a%20similar%20block%2C%20they%20simply%20backed%20off.%20No%20circumvention.%20No%20masking.%20No%20backdoor%20crawling%2C%20according%20to%20Cloudflare%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd570107-028a-4220-a4bd-a5697ea7b32c%5C%22%3EThe%20Fallout%3A%20De-verification%20and%20blocking%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20these%20findings%2C%20Cloudflare%20has%20de-listed%20Perplexity%20as%20a%20verified%20bot%20and%20rolled%20out%20new%20detection%20and%20blocking%20techniques%20across%20its%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECloudflare's%20takedown%20serves%20as%20a%20cautionary%20tale%20in%20the%20AI%20arms%20race.%20While%20the%20web%20shifts%20toward%20stronger%20control%20over%20data%20access%20and%20usage%2C%20actors%20who%20flout%20these%20evolving%20norms%20may%20find%20themselves%20not%20just%20blocked%2C%20but%20publicly%20called%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20where%20AI%20systems%20are%20hungry%20for%20training%20data%2C%20Cloudflare's%20sting%20operation%20is%20a%20signal%20to%20startups%20and%20established%20players%20alike%3A%20Respect%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20web%2C%20or%20risk%20being%20exposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESign%20up%20for%20BI's%20Tech%20Memo%20newsletter%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Ftech-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Reach%20out%20to%20me%20via%20email%20at%2